Very cool concept!<p>I spent a while tweaking the code to get more CPU cycles, but after a while tired of mining the asteroids manually, so I just got rid of them:<p><pre><code>  ENGINE.Game.spawnAsteroid = function () {}
</code></pre>
After that the next logical step was to give myself more ships:<p><pre><code>  SHIP_CPU_COST = 0.001;
</code></pre>
Of course, it&#x27;s a lot more interesting (and challenging!) to actually play by the rules.

1. List (very real) benefits of going to college.
2. Repeatedly refuse to engage in any sort of analysis of whether those benefits were justified by their cost by using phrases like &quot;I can&#x27;t even put a price on those experiences.&quot;
3. Claim that college is worth every penny.<p>&quot;College is just a means to a higher salary&quot; is a strawman. The real question is whether the other things it brings are worth tying yourself down in heavy debt for most of your working life.<p>Also, if a big reason to go to college is motivation you can&#x27;t find anywhere else, how completely f<i></i>*ed will you be when you enter the real world heavily in debt and unable to learn new things without paying an institution thousands of dollars per month to motivate you?
